The paper discusses security threats in Bluetooth-enabled mobile devices, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and network security (cs.NI). The use of pen-testing software and analysis of vulnerabilities also suggests a focus on software engineering (cs.SE) and system engineering (cs.SY). Additionally, the use of various devices such as mobile phones and wireless headsets indicates a possible connection to multimedia (cs.MM) as well.
